This article is a presidential proclamation by President Barack Obama declaring September 16, 2011, as National POW/MIA Recognition Day. The proclamation acknowledges the sacrifices made by American service members who have been prisoners of war or have gone missing in action. It emphasizes the commitment to never give up the search for those held as prisoners of war or missing and to care for their families. The proclamation also mentions the raising of a black and white banner symbolizing America's Missing in Action and Prisoners of War at various locations across the country. The president urges all Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.